      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(web_fetch): strip whitespace from URLs to prevent new URL() parse errors",
        "body": "\n## Summary\n\nFixes #91651: LLMs occasionally generate `web_fetch` URLs with accidental spaces (e.g. `\"https:// docs.example.com/page\"`) which cause `new URL()` to throw `Invalid URL: must be http or https`.\n\n**Revised approach** (per ClawSweeper review): Instead of unconditionally stripping all whitespace, the fix uses try-catch fallback:\n1. Try `new URL(params.url)` first — preserves standard percent-encoding for valid URLs\n2. Only if parsing fails, fall back to whitespace-stripped URL — recovers from LLM-generated space typos\n3. This ensures valid URLs with path/query spaces (e.g. `https://example.com/a%20b`) keep their percent-encoding instead of being silently rewritten\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #91651\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** `web_fetch` tool rejects URLs with accidental internal whitespace (LLM generation artifact). Old approach was too aggressive (stripped all whitespace, breaking valid URLs). New try-catch approach preserves valid URL semantics.\n- **Real environment tested:** macOS, Node v22.22.3, latest upstream/main (050c0813b)\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```bash\nnode proof-91693.mjs\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix (copied live output):**\n\n```\n=== URL Parsing Fix: try-catch fallback ===\n\nCase 1: LLM-generated whitespace\n  Input:  \"https:// docs.example.com/page\"\n  Raw URL() throws: true\n  Recovered href: https://docs.example.com/page\n  PASS: true\n\nCase 2: Tab after scheme\n  Input:  \"https://\\texample.com/path\"\n  Recovered href: https://example.com/path\n  PASS: true\n\nCase 3: Valid URL with path/query spaces\n  Input:  \"https://example.com/a b/search?q=hello world\"\n  Raw URL() succeeds: true\n  Result href: https://example.com/a%20b/search?q=hello%20world\n  Path spaces encoded: true  Query spaces encoded: true\n  PASS: true (spaces preserved as %20, NOT stripped)\n\nCase 4: Normal URL (no-op)\n  Input:  \"https://example.com/normal\"\n  Result href: https://example.com/normal\n  PASS: true\n\n=== Live HTTP fetch with space-stripped URL ===\n\nMalformed URL: \"https:// example.com\"\nCleaned URL:   \"https://example.com\"\nHTTP status: 200\nContent-length: chunked\nBody preview: <!doctype html><html lang=\"en\"><head><title>Example Domain</title>...\nLive fetch: PASS\n\n=== URL parsing: ALL PASSED ===\n=== Proof #91693: COMPLETE ===\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** Malformed URLs are recovered via whitespace stripping, while valid URLs with path/query spaces retain correct percent-encoding. Live HTTP fetch confirms the cleaned URL resolves.\n- **What was not tested:** All HTTP URLs that could be affected by whitespace removal (infinite combinatorial space). The fix uses standard URL parser behavior for valid URLs.\n- **Proof limitations or environment constraints:** Live fetch depends on network access; URL parsing logic is deterministic and verified across 4 edge cases.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n**Which commands did you run?**\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/tools/web-fetch.cf-markdown.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n# 9 passed (1 test file, includes new \"preserves valid path/query spaces as percent-encoding\" test)\n```\n\n**What regression coverage was added or updated?**\n- `\"recovers from URLs with accidental internal whitespace (#91651)\"` — fetches URL with space after scheme, verifies cleanup\n- `\"preserves valid path/query spaces as percent-encoding\"` — verifies valid path/query spaces are percent-encoded, NOT stripped\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n**Did user-visible behavior change?** Yes — URLs with internal whitespace now succeed instead of throwing errors, while valid URLs with path/query spaces are unchanged.\n**Did config, environment, or migration behavior change?** No\n**Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change?** No\n**What is the highest-risk area?** Try-catch fallback could mask different URL parse errors. Mitigation: second parse only strips whitespace (same operation as before), and SSRF guard still validates the parsed URL.\n**How is that risk mitigated?** Protocol check and SSRF validation remain after parsed URL is obtained. Invalid URLs that are not fixed by whitespace removal still throw.\n\n## Current review state\n\n**What is the next action?** Requesting ClawSweeper re-review.\n**What is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?** None — proof updated with live URL parsing demo + real HTTP fetch.\n\n---\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com>\n",
